<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>

<section xml:id="I5" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
    <title>I5: Computing Definite Integrals</title>
    <objectives>
        <dl>
            <li>
                <title>I5</title>
                <p>
                    I can use the Second Fundamental Theorem of Calculus to compute definite integrals.
                </p>
            </li>
        </dl>
    </objectives>

    <xi:include href="./preparation/I5-prep.ptx" />

    <subsection xml:id="I5-activities">
        <title>In-Class Activities</title>

        <remark>
            <p>
                <xref ref="I3"/> has us compute integrals by hand; this process is tedious, and can be avoided by using <xref ref="thm-ftc2"/>.
            </p>
        </remark>

        <theorem xml:id="thm-ftc2">
            <title>Fundamental Theorem of Calculus (Part 2)</title>
            <idx><h>fundamental theorem of calculus (part 2)</h></idx>
            <statement>
                <p>
                    If <m>f(x)</m> is continuous on <m>[a,b]</m> with antiderivative <m>F(x)</m> on <m>[a,b]</m>, then
                    <me>
                        \ds \int_a^b f(x)\, dx = F(b) - F(a)
                    </me>
                </p>
            </statement>
        </theorem>

        <activity xml:id="i-activity-ftc2-1">
            <introduction>
                <p>
                    Compute the value of each definite integral below.
                </p>
            </introduction>
            <task>
                <statement>
                    <p>
                        <m>
                            \ds \int_{-2}^1 x^3\,dx
                        </m>
                    </p>
                </statement>
            </task>
            <task>
                <statement>
                    <p>
                        <m>
                            \ds \int_0^{1} \dfrac{1}{1+x^2}\, dx
                        </m>
                    </p>
                </statement>
            </task>
            <task>
                <statement>
                    <p>
                        <m>
                            \ds \int_1^3 (x^2+2x-4)\, dx
                        </m>
                    </p>
                </statement>
            </task>
            <task>
                <statement>
                    <p>
                        <m>
                            \ds \int_1^e \dfrac{1}{x} + e^x\, dx
                        </m>
                    </p>
                </statement>
            </task>
            <task>
                <statement>
                    <p>
                        <m>
                            \ds \int_1^9 \sqrt{x}\,dx
                        </m>
                    </p>
                </statement>
            </task>
            <task>
                <statement>
                    <p>
                        <m>
                            \ds \int_{\pi/4}^{\pi/3} \csc^2\theta\, d\theta
                        </m>
                    </p>
                </statement>
            </task>
            <task>
                <statement>
                    <p>
                        <m>
                            \ds \int_{\pi/6}^{\pi/2}\csc t\cot t\, dt
                        </m>
                    </p>
                </statement>
            </task>
            <task>
                <statement>
                    <p>
                        Determine <m>\ds \int_{-\pi/4}^{\pi/2} \cos x - \sin x\, dx</m>
                    </p>
                </statement>
            </task>
        </activity>

        <activity xml:id="i-activity-ftc2-continuity">
            <statement>
                <p>
                    Is the statement <m>\ds \int_{-1}^1 \dfrac{1}{x^3}\, dx = 0</m> correct?  Why or why not?
                </p>
            </statement>
        </activity>

        <activity xml:id="i-activity-ftc2-3">
            <statement>
                <p>
                    Find the area bounded by the curves <m>y = e^x-2</m>, <m>x=0</m> and <m>x=1</m>.
                </p>
            </statement>
        </activity>

    </subsection>

</section>